Please share with everybody at least 1 aspect you like and dislike about the town of Blacksburg. (eg Duckpond, TOTs, etc.) You may justify your pick and discuss it with others.

You may start now and let me know when you’re finished
College town => Noise
I enjoy the size of the town of Blacksburg, I think it is small enough to have the feel of a smaller town, but it still has most of the stores and amenities I enjoy
I dislike it's location, it is not as close to other major cities as I would like

I like how Blacksburg is not too busy like a big city, but still has a sense of life in it. However, I do feel like there is a lack of activities to do within the city itself. You need to venture out to other areas to do a lot of other things.
I like the Farmer's Market in Blacksburg a lot - it feels very local and has a great sense of community
I enjoy spending time at Hahn Horticulture garden and driving around the city. Sometime it feels like I am so close to earth.
I dislike that there isn't a lot to do around Blacksburg - you have maybe 5 bars but you have to go to Christiansburg or Roanoke to do much else
Yeah I agree. I have to go to Christiansburg for more mainstream stores
Or Roanoke if I want to go further
Agreed about stores, I wish that there was a larger general store like a Walmart in Blacksburg
I agree
I heard Blacksburg promotes smaller locally owned stores, but that usually raises the prices around here.
Sometime I don't like the frequently changing weather in Blacksburg mostly the wind.
Yeah, the winters can be kinda brutal here
That's pretty common in SW VA.
For sure, the weather here is all over the place
agreed, since as college students we are frequently walking around campus the weather can be very annoying
It's kind of nice how the plants and trees change colors, but the amount of pollen on campus gets to me during the spring semester
